Governor Cyprian Awiti has expressed concern over cash crunch facing his government. He revealed that they had not got devolved funds from the Government for two months, a situation threatening to paralyse operations. ALSO READ:

Petitioners pay Sh500m after losing election cases The governor said the situation had made it difficult to pay workers’ salaries. “It is March 17 but our workers have not received their February salaries. We have been forced to write letters to request them to wait until we receive the devolved funds,” Awiti said